    <title>RADCore</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="namespaceRADCore" kindref="compound">RADCore</ref> is the foundation module. It provides the event system, connection handles, event loops, timers, cross-thread invocation helpers, IO devices, memory buffers, files, binary data streams, JSON, settings, filesystem utilities, futures, and compact value primitives. Everything lives in the <computeroutput><ref refid="namespaceRADCore" kindref="compound">RADCore</ref></computeroutput> namespace.</para>
<para>The event system is built on <computeroutput>RADObject</computeroutput>, the base class that tracks thread affinity and auto-disconnects connections when a receiver is destroyed. Typed events are declared with the <computeroutput><ref refid="RADCore_8h_1a6834046ef184f6f1f29ac61c42919a6c" kindref="member">RAD_EVENT(name, (Args...))</ref></computeroutput> macro and wired with <computeroutput>RADCONNECT</computeroutput>/<computeroutput>RADCONNECT_QUEUED</computeroutput>; <computeroutput>Event::connect()</computeroutput> delivers directly on the receiver&apos;s thread while <computeroutput>connect_queued()</computeroutput> posts through an explicit <computeroutput>EventLoop</computeroutput>. Connections are represented by the <computeroutput>Connection</computeroutput> handle returned from <computeroutput>connect()</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><computeroutput>EventLoop</computeroutput> is the task loop, selectable between the locked <computeroutput>RADEVENT_LOCK</computeroutput> and low-latency <computeroutput>RADEVENT_NOLOCK</computeroutput> strategies, with <computeroutput>post()</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>postDelayed()</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>exec()</computeroutput>, and <computeroutput><ref refid="namespaceRADUi_1ae14f432fc7f4403737def2488fb7485c" kindref="member">quit()</ref></computeroutput>. <computeroutput>EventLoopHandle</computeroutput> is a weak posting handle safe to keep beyond the loop&apos;s lifetime, and <computeroutput><ref refid="namespaceRADCore_1a84e87efd909b8e13061f60584277b55d" kindref="member">singleShot()</ref></computeroutput>, <computeroutput><ref refid="namespaceRADCore_1ac4371b61cc355e9e15f5c83f53ec6ff4" kindref="member">invoke()</ref></computeroutput>, and <computeroutput><ref refid="namespaceRADCore_1a33faa1988fcf26ad66804f4dcd8dbec9" kindref="member">invokeBlocking()</ref></computeroutput> are free-function helpers for cross-thread work. <computeroutput>RADElapsedTimer</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>RADDeadlineTimer</computeroutput>, and the <computeroutput>RADCancellationSource</computeroutput>/<computeroutput>RADCancellationToken</computeroutput> pair cover timing and cooperative cancellation.</para>
<para>IO is modeled on the abstract <computeroutput>RADIODevice</computeroutput>, with <computeroutput>RADFile</computeroutput> and in-memory <computeroutput>RADBuffer</computeroutput> implementations, <computeroutput>OpenMode</computeroutput> flags, and <computeroutput>RADDataStream</computeroutput> for endian-aware binary serialization. Structured returns use <computeroutput>RADResult&lt;T&gt;</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>RADError</computeroutput> rather than exceptions. Data primitives include <computeroutput>RADVariant</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>RADDateTime</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>RADUuid</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>RADUrl</computeroutput>, and the <computeroutput>RADJsonValue</computeroutput>/<computeroutput>RADJsonDocument</computeroutput> JSON tree, with <computeroutput><ref refid="namespaceRADSettings" kindref="compound">RADSettings</ref></computeroutput> layering a JSON-file-backed key/value store on top. Filesystem helpers live in the <computeroutput><ref refid="namespaceRADCore_1_1FileSystem" kindref="compound">RADCore::FileSystem</ref></computeroutput> namespace, alongside RAII <computeroutput>RADTemporaryDirectory</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>RADTemporaryFile</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>RADLockFile</computeroutput>, and the <computeroutput>RADFileSystemWatcher</computeroutput> (inotify-backed). <computeroutput>RADFuture</computeroutput>/<computeroutput>RADFutureT&lt;T&gt;</computeroutput> wrap shared futures for async results.</para>
<para><ref refid="namespaceRADCore" kindref="compound">RADCore</ref> also exposes runtime build introspection through <computeroutput><ref refid="namespaceRADCore_1a92bbfe1d560471f6014f5b5d5a2d4d1b" kindref="member">runtimeEdition()</ref></computeroutput>, <computeroutput><ref refid="namespaceRADCore_1aa673e9453fb6ebe58dab078ba2b2ce4c" kindref="member">runtimeRequiresLicenseKey()</ref></computeroutput>, and <computeroutput><ref refid="namespaceRADCore_1abd370291b54323d3fd0003c1c679e69f" kindref="member">runtimeAuditStamp()</ref></computeroutput> (defined in <computeroutput>RADCoreExtras.cpp</computeroutput>), which report the edition and license expectations of the loaded library for diagnostics.</para>
<sect1 id="md__media_jvincent_Kingspec512_repos_RADLib_docs_public_radcore_1autotoc_md6">
<title>Core features</title>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><computeroutput>RADObject</computeroutput> + <computeroutput>RAD_EVENT</computeroutput>/<computeroutput>RADCONNECT</computeroutput> typed events with automatic cleanup.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>EventLoop</computeroutput> (locked and lock-free strategies) with <computeroutput>EventLoopHandle</computeroutput> posting.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>RADIODevice</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>RADFile</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>RADBuffer</computeroutput>, and endian-aware <computeroutput>RADDataStream</computeroutput>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>RADJsonValue</computeroutput>/<computeroutput>RADJsonDocument</computeroutput> and JSON-backed <computeroutput><ref refid="namespaceRADSettings" kindref="compound">RADSettings</ref></computeroutput>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>RADResult&lt;T&gt;</computeroutput>/<computeroutput>RADError</computeroutput>, plus <computeroutput>RADVariant</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>RADDateTime</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>RADUuid</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>RADUrl</computeroutput>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput><ref refid="namespaceRADCore_1_1FileSystem" kindref="compound">RADCore::FileSystem</ref></computeroutput> helpers, RAII temp files/locks, <computeroutput>RADFileSystemWatcher</computeroutput>.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Beta notes:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>File watching and process/PTY helpers are Linux-first in this beta.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>RADFuture</computeroutput>/<computeroutput>RADFutureT</computeroutput> and other threaded helpers are excluded from <computeroutput>RADLIB_EMBEDDED</computeroutput> builds.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Example:</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".cpp"><codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="classRADCore_1_1EventLoop" kindref="compound">RADCore::EventLoop</ref><sp/>loop(<ref refid="namespaceRADCore_1a015a8065c217ebb2629d983d7fb550f5" kindref="member">RADCore::RADEVENT_LOCK</ref>);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="classRADCore_1_1RADFile" kindref="compound">RADCore::RADFile</ref><sp/>file(</highlight><highlight class="stringliteral">&quot;config.json&quot;</highlight><highlight class="normal">);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="keywordflow">if</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>(file.open(<ref refid="namespaceRADCore_1aefc7037828eebd6f6c85bda2ea2b2852a131fb182a881796e7606ed6da27f1197" kindref="member">RADCore::OpenMode::ReadOnly</ref>))<sp/>{</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/></highlight><highlight class="keyword">auto</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>bytes<sp/>=<sp/>file.readAll();</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>std::string<sp/>text(bytes.begin(),<sp/>bytes.end());</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/></highlight><highlight class="keywordflow">if</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>(</highlight><highlight class="keyword">auto</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>doc<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="classRADCore_1_1RADJsonDocument_1a87332eff24cd5977124634d4d079d2b6" kindref="member">RADCore::RADJsonDocument::fromJson</ref>(text))<sp/>{</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/></highlight><highlight class="keyword">const</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/></highlight><highlight class="keyword">auto</highlight><highlight class="normal">&amp;<sp/>root<sp/>=<sp/>doc-&gt;root();</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><ref refid="RADCore_8h_1a9b7f86af1c42e10d0ce826c5e81ee8d1" kindref="member">RADInfo</ref>()<sp/>&lt;&lt;<sp/></highlight><highlight class="stringliteral">&quot;port<sp/>=<sp/>&quot;</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>&lt;&lt;<sp/>root[</highlight><highlight class="stringliteral">&quot;port&quot;</highlight><highlight class="normal">].toInt(8080);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>}</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">}</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="namespaceRADCore_1a84e87efd909b8e13061f60584277b55d" kindref="member">RADCore::singleShot</ref>(250,<sp/>loop,<sp/>[&amp;loop]<sp/>{<sp/>loop.quit();<sp/>});</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">loop.exec();</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> </para>
